<p>While no details were immediately available of the deal, Bloomberg reports that the deal was initially touted more than one year ago by the French government as <strong>being valued at as much as $18 billion.</strong></p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/zerohedge/feed/~4/O02g7ocIJ1Q" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 25 Mar 2019 12:17:14 -0400";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:12:"Tyler Durden";}s:4:"guid";s:92:"https://www.zerohedge.com/news/2019-03-25/boeing-shares-dip-airbus-seals-massive-order-china";s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:92:"https://www.zerohedge.com/news/2019-03-25/boeing-shares-dip-airbus-seals-massive-order-china";}s:7:"summary";s:4668:"<p>The last few days have seen Boeing shares roller-coaster on market swings and idiosyncratic headlines (as Garuda started the worrying trend of canceling airplane orders). Today, Boeing shares slipped after Bloomberg reported that <strong>Airbus has secured a long-awaited aircraft order from China</strong>.</p>

